        "103": {
          "vnum": 103,
          "name": "The Eastern Road",
          "description": "As you trudge along the road, you notice that you have reached the crest of the hill. From this vantage point, you can see past the opposing hill which bounds the river to the south and into the open grasslands beyond. The road slopes gradually downward to the east, and more sharply so to the west. The grasses to the south lead into the heavily wooded river valley between the hills. Just off the road to the north, you spot a small circle of standing stones.",
