        "104": {
          "vnum": 104,
          "name": "Riverbank",
          "description": "The River of Bruenor's Woe flows just east of here, meandering southward down the grassy slopes before dropping sharply into the wooded river valley. A road leads in from the west to a point in the river where stones have been placed to allow easy crossing. Beyond the stones, you spot the beginnings of another road. A dirt path leads north along the riverside, and the grassy slopes follow it to the south. Breathing deeply, you run... Bruenor's Crossing You stand on stones placed carefully into the waters of the river. Though worn smooth by ages of water, they yet provide adequate footing to avoid the chill waters and powerful current. In the middle of the river, a large stone rises above the others, and has been marked with a placard of bronze. The river runs north and south, and roads run to the banks on either side. Breathing deeply, you run... Dusty Road Tiny vortices of wind-spun dust dance at the edges of this rutted road, sending grains of earth settling into the empty ditches that line it. To the west is the chatter of a wide, shallow river, while to the east the dust-devils spin their preoccupied minuets. Breathing deeply, you run... Dusty Road A matted yellow mohawk of grass limply divides the two wide and barren swaths of dirt which make up this road. The road abruptly curves into a pasture and turns into a wide and muddy footpath to the north, and thirstily crawls toward a river to the west. You can't go that way. You can't go that way. You can't go that way. You can't go that way.",
